cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.NA, cs.DS 

The paper deals with visual recognition tasks, which suggests that it belongs to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes methods for sparse coding and dictionary learning, which are common topics in machine learning (cs.LG) and information theory (cs.IT). The use of Riemannian manifolds also suggests that the paper may belong to the numerical analysis (cs.NA) sub-category. Lastly, the paper presents experiments on classification tasks, which could also place it in the data structures (cs.DS) sub-category.
